{"id": "duc04-testb-38:6#18", "contents": "Iran has offered to mediate between Syria and Turkey in their deepening dispute over Kurdish rebel bases. Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi made the mediation offer in a telephone conversation with his Syrian counterpart, Farouk al-Sharaa. Iran plans to dispatch envoys to the two countries, although a specific date has not been announced. This development comes as tensions between Turkey and Syria, Iran's closest Arab ally, have escalated in recent days. Ankara has sent troops to its border with Syria, prompting fears of an attack."}
